      <div type="commentary" xml:lang="eng">
	<p>This edition is based on Andrew Ollett’s reading of the inscription <hi rend="italic">in situ</hi> and photographs taken in February 2017.</p>
	<p>The <hi rend="italic">anusvāra</hi> is written to the right, along the top line of the <hi rend="italic">akṣara</hi>.</p>
      </div>
      <div type="edition" xml:lang="pra-Latn">
	<ab>
	  <lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" extent="12" unit="character" precision="low"/>
	  ya <persName key="pers:Be-Gobhūti">gobhūtinaṃ</persName> 
	  āraṇakāna peḍapātikānaṃ 
	  <placeName key="pl:Mārakuḍa">mārakuḍa</placeName>vāsinaṃ thupo
	  <lb n="2"/><gap reason="lost" extent="10" unit="character" precision="low"/><supplied reason="lost" resp="#ASWI4">aṃte</supplied>vāsinā <persName key="pers:Be-Āṣāḍhamitra">bhatāsāḷamitena</persName>
	  kārita
	</ab>
      </div>
      <div type="translation" xml:lang="eng">
	<ab>
	  The <hi rend="italic">stūpa</hi> of 
	  <persName key="pers:Be-Gobhūti">Gobhūti</persName>,
	  the forest-dweller and mendicant from 
	  <placeName key="pl:Beḍsā">Mārakuḍa</placeName> ... caused to be made by [his student], the devoted
	  <persName key="pers:Be-Āṣāḍhamitra">Āṣāḍhamitra</persName>.
	</ab>
      </div>
